Popular Yoruba actor Odunlade Adekola has left a fan utterly mind blown by his gesture. The fan, a media personality simply identified as Layi, was awestruck to finally meet the actor who he referred to as a legend. A video shared on Layi’s Twitter page sees the renowned movie star walking into a room with his humble fan comes with head bowed and then dropped to his knees to greet him. Adekola beckoned on Layi to stand but he insisted on remaining on his knees forcing the actor to do what further dazed him.   Flavour consoles white lady scammed by impersonator     Comedienne Princess reacts to Baba Ijesha’s sentence     Olamide gives fan N2.4million wristwatch   Seeing Layi stayed insistent on kneeling for him, the comic actor also dropped to his knees. They got up at the same time and hugged each other. Captioning the beautiful video, Layi expressed how blissful his life has been in recent times noting he trust God to perfect what He’s started. “Lately I’ve been watching my life like a movie directed by God. I have no idea where it’s headed but I’m sure it’s an expected end. Twitter family! Layi don meet legend o as scripted by the Almighty,” he wrote.